      "content": "\"Pre-approved contingency planning\"? That sounds like a very convenient way to categorize it. Look, if I take this to the committee and tell them everything is fine, and then we see actual movement on the ground tomorrow, it's my head on the line—and the stability of the entire administration. \n\nJust give it to me straight, off the record: if you had to bet on the likelihood of a full-scale kinetic event in the next 48 hours, would you say it's still \"low,\" or are you just telling me what you think I need to hear to keep things calm?",
